{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the main objectives of this review paper are to address and focus valuable insight into hyperspectral image reconstruction using deep learning-based techniques for applications in the agri-food domain towards contributing to global food security and food quality and safety issues through advanced data processing and technological advancement.",
    "HSI was originally developed by NASA for remote sensing applications in space exploration and earth observation.",
    "Over time, HSI technology has evolved and expanded into various fields, including agriculture (Wang et al. 2021a (Wang et al., 2023)), food quality evaluation (Ahmed et al. 2023a; Sun et al. 2024), medical imaging (Zhang et al. 2024), environmental monitoring (Peyghambari and Zhang 2021) and so on (Ahmed et al. 2023a; He and Sun 2015).",
    "The technology combines imaging and spectroscopy in one system to simultaneously capture both spatial and spectral information and generates a complete spectrum for each pixel in an image (ElMasry and Sun 2010).",
    "Unlike traditional RGB imaging, which captures only color bands, HSI acquires hundreds of narrow spectral bands across a range of spectral wavelengths."
  ]
}